## Image traceability

- Avoid `latest` for real validation because mutable image references weaken reproducibility.
- Prefer immutable version tags or digests for release candidates.
- Use Trivy readiness from the supply-chain module to prepare vulnerability scanning.
- Use Syft readiness from the supply-chain module to prepare SBOM generation.
- Treat Cosign signing as optional readiness unless the image reference is registry-backed.

## Runtime hardening recommendations

Review the generated Deployment for these controls:

- run the container as a non-root user;
- set `readOnlyRootFilesystem: true` where the application allows it;
- drop Linux capabilities with `capabilities.drop: ["ALL"]`;
- keep `privileged: false`;
- set `allowPrivilegeEscalation: false`;
- define CPU and memory requests and limits;
- define readiness and liveness probes;
- keep image pull policy coherent with the tag strategy.

